# React Frontend Conventions (Marketplace / Kloud)

React 19 + React Router 7 + Vite 6 + TypeScript + Tailwind 4.

## Page and Component Structure

- Views/pages live in `src/pages/`.
- When creating a new page, also create the React Router mapping.
- Each major block of a page gets its own component file in `src/components/`.
- Reusable components that are not in `src/components/ui/` get their own file.

## UI Patterns

- All UI components use shadcn (Radix UI + Tailwind).
- All buttons that call endpoints MUST show a loading state.
- Destructive operations MUST show a confirmation dialog.
- All backend interaction notifications use sonner toasts.

## API Integration

- Use `callApi()` for all endpoint calls.
- When building a view, also write the relevant backend endpoints.

## Forms and Validation

- react-hook-form for form state management.
- Zod schemas for validation.

## Styling

- Tailwind CSS 4 with `@tailwindcss/vite`.
- Radix UI primitives for accessible components.

## Note on Layout

The marketplace is a desktop admin app — it is NOT mobile-first (unlike msg-guest and msg-guide).
